text.tspan: Wouldnt it be nice to look at a pleasant artwork instead of
a black space when your TV is not in use? The Samsung
Frame TV offers this feature. However, an artwork screen
that is always on would also consume a lot of energy.
Thats why the device contains a radar sensor that can
detect people in the room and turns off the art mode once
nobody is around. This not only saves OLED lifetime but
